verses.text_plain: Then Jonah prayed unto the Lord his God out of the fish’s belly,
verses.verse_html: 1Then Jonah prayed unto the Lord his God out of the fish’s belly,

verses.text_plain: And said, I cried by reason of mine affliction unto the Lord, and he heard me; out of the belly of hell cried I, and thou heardest my voice.
verses.verse_html:
2And said, I cried by reason of mine affliction unto the Lord, and he heard me; out of the belly of hell cried I, and thou heardest my voice. ▼
▼ by…: or, out of mine affliction
 , ▼
▼ hell: or, the grave

footnotes.body_text: ▼ by…: or, out of mine affliction
footnotes.body_html: ▼ by…: or, out of mine affliction
▼ hell: or, the grave

verses.text_plain: For thou hadst cast me into the deep, in the midst of the seas; and the floods compassed me about: all thy billows and thy waves passed over me.
verses.verse_html:
3For thou hadst cast me into the deep, in the midst of the seas; and the floods compassed me about: all thy billows and thy waves passed over me. ▼
▼ midst: Heb. heart

verses.text_plain: Then I said, I am cast out of thy sight; yet I will look again toward thy holy temple.
verses.verse_html: 4Then I said, I am cast out of thy sight; yet I will look again toward thy holy temple.

verses.text_plain: The waters compassed me about, even to the soul: the depth closed me round about, the weeds were wrapped about my head.
verses.verse_html: 5The waters compassed me about, even to the soul: the depth closed me round about, the weeds were wrapped about my head.

verses.text_plain: I went down to the bottoms of the mountains; the earth with her bars was about me for ever: yet hast thou brought up my life from corruption, O Lord my God.
verses.verse_html:
6I went down to the bottoms of the mountains; the earth with her bars was about me for ever: yet hast thou brought up my life from corruption, O Lord my God. ▼
▼ bottoms: Heb. cuttings off
 , ▼
▼ corruption: or, the pit

footnotes.body_html: ▼ bottoms: Heb. cuttings off
▼ corruption: or, the pit

verses.text_plain: When my soul fainted within me I remembered the Lord: and my prayer came in unto thee, into thine holy temple.
verses.verse_html: 7When my soul fainted within me I remembered the Lord: and my prayer came in unto thee, into thine holy temple.

verses.text_plain: They that observe lying vanities forsake their own mercy.
verses.verse_html: 8They that observe lying vanities forsake their own mercy.

verses.text_plain: But I will sacrifice unto thee with the voice of thanksgiving; I will pay that that I have vowed. Salvation is of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 9But I will sacrifice unto thee with the voice of thanksgiving; I will pay that that I have vowed. Salvation is of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto the fish, and it vomited out Jonah upon the dry land.
verses.verse_html: 10And the Lord spake unto the fish, and it vomited out Jonah upon the dry land.
